Livery stable, 608 West 48th Street, south side, west of Eleventh
Avenue.
April 21, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.

614 West 48th Street, west of the S.W. corner of Eleventh Ave.
April 21, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

(1)
616-626 West 48th Street, south side, between Eleventh and Twelfth Aves. No. 626 is a 2-story frame house.
April 21, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
A view at the Hudson River extremity of 48th Street. Note the new French Line Terminal (Pier No. 88) and the also new "Normandie" alongside. Frame structure (No. 626) is distinctly apparent on the left.
June 5, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.
